<h2 id=3D"custom-instructions-in-use-1" tabindex=3D"-1"><a class=3D"heading=
-link" href=3D"https://docs.github.com/en/copilot/how-tos/configure-custom-=
instructions/add-repository-instructions#custom-instructions-in-use-1">Cust=
om instructions in use<span class=3D"heading-link-symbol" aria-hidden=3D"tr=
ue"></span></a></h2>
<p>The instructions in the file(s) are available for use by Copilot as soon=
 as you save the file(s). Instructions are automatically added to requests =
that you submit to Copilot.</p>
<p>Custom instructions are not visible in the Chat view or inline chat, but=
 you can verify that they are being used by Copilot by looking at the Refer=
ences list of a response in the Chat view. If custom instructions were adde=
d to the prompt that was sent to the model, the <code>.github/copilot-instr=
uctions.md</code> file is listed as a reference. You can click the referenc=
e to open the file.</p>
<p><picture><source srcset=3D"/assets/cb-28337/mw-1440/images/help/copilot/=
custom-instructions-vscode.webp 2x" type=3D"image/webp"><img src=3D"https:/=
/docs.github.com/assets/cb-28337/images/help/copilot/custom-instructions-vs=
code.png" alt=3D"Screenshot of an expanded References list, showing the 'co=
pilot-instructions.md' file highlighted with a dark orange outline."></pict=
ure></p>
<h2 id=3D"enabling-or-disabling-repository-custom-instructions" tabindex=3D=
"-1"><a class=3D"heading-link" href=3D"https://docs.github.com/en/copilot/h=
ow-tos/configure-custom-instructions/add-repository-instructions#enabling-o=
r-disabling-repository-custom-instructions">Enabling or disabling repositor=
y custom instructions<span class=3D"heading-link-symbol" aria-hidden=3D"tru=
e"></span></a></h2>
<p>You can choose whether or not you want Copilot to use repository-based c=
ustom instructions.</p>
<h3 id=3D"enabling-or-disabling-custom-instructions-for-copilot-chat" tabin=
dex=3D"-1"><a class=3D"heading-link" href=3D"https://docs.github.com/en/cop=
ilot/how-tos/configure-custom-instructions/add-repository-instructions#enab=
ling-or-disabling-custom-instructions-for-copilot-chat">Enabling or disabli=
ng custom instructions for Copilot Chat<span class=3D"heading-link-symbol" =
aria-hidden=3D"true"></span></a></h3>
<p>Custom instructions are enabled for Copilot Chat by default but you can =
disable, or re-enable, them at any time. This applies to your own use of Co=
pilot Chat and does not affect other users.</p>
<ol>
<li>Open the Setting editor by using the keyboard shortcut <kbd>Command</kb=
d>+<kbd>,</kbd> (Mac) / <kbd>Ctrl</kbd>+<kbd>,</kbd> (Linux/Windows).</li>
<li>Type <code>instruction file</code> in the search box.</li>
<li>Select or clear the checkbox under <strong>Code Generation: Use Instruc=
tion Files</strong>.</li>
</ol>
<h3 id=3D"enabling-or-disabling-custom-instructions-for-copilot-code-review=
-1" tabindex=3D"-1"><a class=3D"heading-link" href=3D"https://docs.github.c=
om/en/copilot/how-tos/configure-custom-instructions/add-repository-instruct=
ions#enabling-or-disabling-custom-instructions-for-copilot-code-review-1">E=
nabling or disabling custom instructions for Copilot code review<span class=
