<h2 id=3D"custom-instructions-in-use-2" tabindex=3D"-1"><a class=3D"heading=
-link" href=3D"https://docs.github.com/en/copilot/how-tos/configure-custom-=
instructions/add-repository-instructions#custom-instructions-in-use-2">Cust=
om instructions in use<span class=3D"heading-link-symbol" aria-hidden=3D"tr=
ue"></span></a></h2>
<p>The instructions in the file(s) are available for use by Copilot as soon=
 as you save the file(s). Instructions are automatically added to requests =
that you submit to Copilot.</p>
<p>Custom instructions are not visible in the Chat view or inline chat, but=
 you can verify that they are being used by Copilot by looking at the Refer=
ences list of a response in the Chat view. If custom instructions were adde=
d to the prompt that was sent to the model, the <code>.github/copilot-instr=
uctions.md</code> file is listed as a reference. You can click the referenc=
e to open the file.</p>
<p><picture><source srcset=3D"/assets/cb-24107/mw-1440/images/help/copilot/=
custom-instruction-ref-visual-studio.webp 2x" type=3D"image/webp"><img src=
=3D"https://docs.github.com/assets/cb-24107/images/help/copilot/custom-inst=
ruction-ref-visual-studio.png" alt=3D"Screenshot of the References popup, s=
howing the 'copilot-instructions.md' file highlighted with a dark orange ou=
tline."></picture></p>
<h2 id=3D"enabling-or-disabling-repository-custom-instructions-1" tabindex=
=3D"-1"><a class=3D"heading-link" href=3D"https://docs.github.com/en/copilo=
t/how-tos/configure-custom-instructions/add-repository-instructions#enablin=
g-or-disabling-repository-custom-instructions-1">Enabling or disabling repo=
sitory custom instructions<span class=3D"heading-link-symbol" aria-hidden=
=3D"true"></span></a></h2>
<p>You can choose whether or not you want Copilot to use repository-based c=
ustom instructions.</p>
<h3 id=3D"enabling-or-disabling-custom-instructions-for-copilot-chat-1" tab=
index=3D"-1"><a class=3D"heading-link" href=3D"https://docs.github.com/en/c=
opilot/how-tos/configure-custom-instructions/add-repository-instructions#en=
abling-or-disabling-custom-instructions-for-copilot-chat-1">Enabling or dis=
abling custom instructions for Copilot Chat<span class=3D"heading-link-symb=
ol" aria-hidden=3D"true"></span></a></h3>
<p>Custom instructions are enabled for Copilot Chat by default but you can =
disable, or re-enable, them at any time. This applies to your own use of Co=
pilot Chat and does not affect other users.</p>
<ol>
<li>
<p>In the Visual Studio menu bar, under <strong>Tools</strong>, click <stro=
ng>Options</strong>.</p>
<p></p><div class=3D"procedural-image-wrapper"><picture><source srcset=3D"/=
assets/cb-37169/mw-1440/images/help/copilot/vs-toolbar-options.webp 2x" typ=
e=3D"image/webp"><img src=3D"https://docs.github.com/assets/cb-37169/images=
/help/copilot/vs-toolbar-options.png" alt=3D"Screenshot of the Visual Studi=
o menu bar. The &quot;Tools&quot; menu is expanded, and the &quot;Options&q=
uot; item is highlighted with an orange outline."></picture></div><p></p>
</li>
<li>
<p>In the "Options" dialog, type <code>custom instructions</code> in the se=
arch box, then click <strong>Copilot</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Select or clear the checkbox for <strong>Enable custom instructions to b=
e loaded from .github/copilot-instructions.md files and added to requests</=
strong>.</p>
<p></p><div class=3D"procedural-image-wrapper"><picture><source srcset=3D"/=
assets/cb-102746/mw-1440/images/help/copilot/vs-custom-instructions-option.=
webp 2x" type=3D"image/webp"><img src=3D"https://docs.github.com/assets/cb-=
102746/images/help/copilot/vs-custom-instructions-option.png" alt=3D"Screen=
shot of the Visual Studio Options dialog showing the &quot;Enable custom in=
structions&quot; option checkbox selected."></picture></div><p></p>
</li>
</ol>
<h3 id=3D"enabling-or-disabling-custom-instructions-for-copilot-code-review=
-2" tabindex=3D"-1"><a class=3D"heading-link" href=3D"https://docs.github.c=
om/en/copilot/how-tos/configure-custom-instructions/add-repository-instruct=
ions#enabling-or-disabling-custom-instructions-for-copilot-code-review-2">E=
nabling or disabling custom instructions for Copilot code review<span class=
=3D"heading-link-symbol" aria-hidden=3D"true"></span></a></h3>
<p>Custom instructions are enabled for Copilot code review by default but y=
ou can disable, or re-enable, them in the repository settings on GitHub.com=
. This applies to Copilot's use of custom instructions for all code reviews=
 it performs in this repository.</p>
<ol>
<li>
<p>On GitHub, navigate to the main page of the repository.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Under your repository name, click <strong><svg version=3D"1.1" width=3D"=
