m-instructions/add-repository-instructions#creating-custom-instructions-4">=
Creating custom instructions<span class=3D"heading-link-symbol" aria-hidden=
=3D"true"></span></a></h2>
<p>Xcode supports a single <code>.github/copilot-instructions.md</code> cus=
tom instructions file stored in the repository.</p>
<p>You can create a custom instructions file in your repository via the Cop=
ilot settings page.</p>
<p>Whitespace between instructions is ignored, so the instructions can be w=
ritten as a single paragraph, each on a new line, or separated by blank lin=
es for legibility.</p>
<ol>
<li>Open the GitHub Copilot for Xcode application.</li>
<li>At the top of the application window, under <strong>Settings</strong>, =
click <strong>Advanced</strong>.</li>
<li>To the right of "Custom Instructions", click <strong>Current Workspace<=
/strong> or <strong>Global</strong> to choose whether the custom instructio=
ns apply to the current workspace or all workspaces.</li>
</ol>
